<item>
            <title>[MATH-546] Truncation issue in KMeansPlusPlusClusterer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-546</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The for loop inside KMeansPlusPlusClusterer.chooseInitialClusters defines a variable&lt;br/&gt;
  int sum = 0;&lt;br/&gt;
This variable should have type double, rather than int.  Using an int causes the method to truncate the distances between points to (square roots of) integers.  It&apos;s especially bad when the distances between points are typically less than 1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As an aside, in version 2.2, this bug manifested itself by making the clusterer return empty clusters.  I wonder if the EmptyClusterStrategy would still be necessary if this bug were fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
